main event: A light green elliptical object was observed in flight over Baltimore on April 12, 1964.
interesting points: The object was reported to be climbing and moving from NW to SE at an elevation of 4-6 degrees., The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes before the object disappeared behind clouds., The object was described as the size of a quarter held at arm's length., The investigating official suggested the object could be a satellite, but there were questions about the reliability of the source., The witness was a 22-year-old student who had made a similar report a year prior.
